      "page_number": 2,
      "order_index": 2,
      "order_confidence": 0.98,
      "full_text": "The forest breathed softly as Kael stepped between the ancient oaks. Moss clung to every surface, and the air tasted of rain and forgotten spells. A narrow trail wound deeper into the green, vanishing into a curtain of silver fog. Somewhere ahead, a stream murmured its endless song over smooth stones.",
